oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Gathering in Public Square
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of people and buggies on the public square in Woodbury. A sign for the Woodbury Implement Company is seen in the background. Pictured are Bob Mason (1) and his daughter, Elizabeth (2), Mack Higgins (1880-1960) (3), Palmer Wood and Dr. Mercer McCrary (4), John Quarles (1853-1928) (5), B. Lawrence (6), Dr. M. B. McCrary (7), and George Gilley (1895-1961).
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Carts & wagons; Billboards
